<HEADLINE>
Russian first deputy PM congratulates Chinese national day
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, Sept. 28 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev expressed
congratulations on the Chinese national day, saying that his
country values friendship and cooperation with China and will
further strengthen bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Medvedev made the remarks Thursday evening at the reception of
the Chinese national day held by the Chinese embassy in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
China has achieved enormous achievements in the fields of socio-
economy, science, technology and culture, and held an important
position in the international arena since it was founded on Oct.
1, 1949, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russia-China relations have currently attained to a new level
on the basis of mutual respect and mutual trust, which indicates
great potentials to further such cooperation, Medvedev said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the theme years held in China and Russia
increase bilateral exchanges and promote pragmatic cooperation in
many fields, strengthening mutual understanding of the peoples of
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Russia Liu Guchang lauded the Sino-Russian
relations, which he said are in the best period for a full-scale
and rapid development.
</P>
<P>
The activities conducted under the framework of the theme years
make the peoples of the two nations closer to each other and help
forge a closer cooperation in various areas, Liu said.
</P>
